# cognitive-pipeline bring-up marker (ADR-095 §4).
#
# As long as this file is present, the CI gate `asset-sha256-validate` lets
# the cog ship with `sha256 = "TODO-set-on-publish"` in cog.toml [[assets]].
# This is the legitimate state during the bring-up window — the cog binary
# is built and proxy-tested before the GCS upload of the GGUF assets has
# happened (asset distribution is the deferred next-layer per ADR-095 §4).
#
# The PR that uploads the GGUFs to gs://cognitum-apps/cogs/arm/models/ must:
#   1. Replace the TODO sha256 values in cog.toml with the real digests.
#   2. Delete this marker file.
# Both happen in the same PR so the gate becomes enforcing the moment the
# assets are published.
